  <li id="comment-16680" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/14356212647201456769" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Roving Lemon</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16680"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-11T00:31:51-04:00">Tuesday, May 11, 2010 at 12:31 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I second the Cook&#39;s Illustrated yeasted waffle recipe. I like it because you need to make it the night before, and leave it in the fridge for about 12 hours to rise and develop flavor, which means Sunday breakfast (which is when we always have them) is a cinch even when you&#39;re half asleep. I posted my slightly adapted version of the recipe here: <a href="http://therovinglemon.blogspot.com/2010/03/low-tech.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://therovinglemon.blogspot.com/2010/03/low-tech.html</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=832#comment-16680' data-commentid="16680" data-postid="832" data-belowelement="comment-16680" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Roving Lemon" aria-label='Reply to Roving Lemon'>Reply</a>    </div>
