  <li id="comment-16683" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.atastierspeech.blogspot.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">pam</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16683"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-11T00:46:19-04:00">Tuesday, May 11, 2010 at 12:46 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Quick Vanilla Waffles from Kate Habershon&#39;s book, &#8220;Pancakes and Waffles&#8221; is my favorite.</p>
<p>1 1/2 c flour; 2 t baking powder; 1/2 t salt; 1 T sugar; 3 eggs, separated; 1 c milk; 5 T butter, melted and cooled; 2 t vanilla</p>
<p>Sift dry ingredients. Mix egg yolks, milk, melted butter and vanilla. Add dry to wet and beat until just mixed. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter, but don&#39;t overmix. So good!</p>
    </div>

