    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly!<br />Your Oatmeal Pancake recipe from Jan!  <br />We&#39;ve been using that recipe for golden, chewy waffles w/ a few minor changes: <br />I&#39;ve been using regular milk, instead of buttermilk,  (I delete the baking soda), and add a tsp of vanilla.<br />Try it, I think you&#39;ll be pleased!<br />Another note: If you forget to prep the night before as I have on occasion, I simply warm the milk and then add the oats to soak for a bit (15-30 min.) before adding the rest of the ingredients&#8230;.only slightly more chewy than your original recipe and just as good.<br />Shelley</p>
