    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made a double batch of Joy of Cooking waffles every week for many years, freezing most for the week ahead. I use half whole wheat pastry flour and half white flour, the minimum of fat (and I use oil, not butter), and chocolate chips. Top with plain yogurt, sliced strawberries and a dusting of powdered sugar if you&#39;re not running for the school bus.</p>
    </div>

