    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My favorite, hands down, is from the Fanny Farmer Cookbook. </p>
<p>I&#39;ve also found this works: When the light on the waffle maker turns green, pour in a TBSP of water. Close the lid. Once the steam stops pour the waffle batter in. Do this for each waffle.</p>
    </div>

