    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My favorite waffle recipe is this one: <a href="http://www.cooklocal.com/?p=139" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.cooklocal.com/?p=139</a></p>
<p>You have to make the batter the night before, but they are light and crispy and a bit yeasty. They smell REALLY yeasty so don&#39;t be too worried. They don&#39;t taste as yeasty as they smell when you wake up in the morning. 🙂 </p>
<p>They also freeze and reheat in the toaster well.</p>
