      <p>Huge cheers for the Cook&#39;s Illustrated yeasted waffles.  They are like the best french fry you ever had, only a waffle.  We make a big double batch of batter every Friday night, then pull them out of the fridge Saturday morning, cook them all, and freeze them for the kids to toast for breakfast all week.  Cherished family pleasure.</p>
