    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Waffles are terrible teases, no?  They disappoint far more often than anything.  </p>
<p>My favorite (and only) are yeasted waffles, made famous by Marion Cunningham and riffed on all over.  Crisp, light, ridiculously flavorful, they avoid the awful sog waffles are so good at. </p>
<p>We use Deborah Madison&#39;s version (sorry for the long link, but here: <a href="http://www.remedialeating.com/2009/06/it-is-hard-not-to-love-a-sunrise----even-when-youve-only-caught-it-by-unhappy-accident-on-the-four-am-coattails-of-a-b.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.remedialeating.com/2009/06/it-is-hard-not-to-love-a-sunrise&#8212;-even-when-youve-only-caught-it-by-unhappy-accident-on-the-four-am-coattails-of-a-b.html</a>)</p>
    </div>

