  <li id="comment-16760" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/15305773287880023217" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Laura</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16760"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-11T14:14:45-04:00">Tuesday, May 11, 2010 at 2:14 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I see that you got tons of recipes already but I would like to add this.  One time I made it with hazelnut and added orange zest and served it with warm orange segments, it was delicious.</p>
<p>I wish I remember where I got it, either martha stewart or king arthur&#39;s book.</p>
<p>Buttermilk waffles</p>
<p>Sift together:<br />2 cups pastry flour<br />2 TBS sugar<br />2 tsp baking powder<br />1 tsp baking soda<br />1 tsp salt<br />1/2 C nut meal (optional but highly recommended)</p>
<p>Combine:</p>
<p>2 eggs<br />1 3/4 C buttermilk<br />4 oz butter (melted)<br />2 tsp vanilla extract</p>
<p>Add the wet ingredients to the dry and mix just until incorporated.  Let sit for few minutes and cook according to your waffle maker.</p>
    </div>

