      <p>I see it&#39;s been said, but the regular old Joy of Cooking waffle recipe has never failed for me (unless I accidentally burn them). So much so that I&#39;ve never felt the need to try any others, so I can&#39;t offer any comparisons. But I have made them for friends who have said they&#39;re the best waffles they&#39;ve ever had! It does instruct you to use a baffling 2-7 tbs of butter, which is actually pretty large range when you think about it.</p>
    </div>

