    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/15823313148161185105" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Lea</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16786"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-11T18:58:23-04:00">Tuesday, May 11, 2010 at 6:58 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>If you have some sourdough starter handy, I would recommend trying Nancy Silverton&#39;s recipe for sourdough waffles which is in her book, Breads from the La Brea Bakery (p. 244).  I don&#39;t like how she mixes her ingredients together, so I do the following:</p>
<p>Combine salt, brown sugar, and flour together in mixer bowl.  While paddle is moving, add milk/butter mixture.  Then add white starter.</p>
<p>I&#39;ve never tried yeasted waffles, but I know I&#39;ll never go back to baking powder/baking soda waffles after having made these.</p>
<p>Hope you can give them a try sometime!</p>
    </div>

