  <li id="comment-16807" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/13584912828082137970" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Casey</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16807"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-12T12:51:54-04:00">Wednesday, May 12, 2010 at 12:51 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi Molly and all,<br />My old boss gave me this family recipe after I told him about my &#8220;new&#8221; thrift store waffle maker. It&#39;s my favorite.</p>
<p>Mix in a small bowl:<br />1 3/4 C. milk<br />2 eggs<br />1/4 C. softened butter<br />1/4 C. yogurt<br />2 tsp. vanilla</p>
<p>Mix in a larger bowl:<br />1 C. white flour<br />3/4 C. whole wheat flour<br />1 Tbsp. baking powder<br />2 Tbsp. sugar</p>
<p>Add contents of small bowl to larger bowl and stir until just mixed. Waffletize.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=832#comment-16807' data-commentid="16807" data-postid="832" data-belowelement="comment-16807" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Casey" aria-label='Reply to Casey'>Reply</a>    </div>
