      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16863"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-17T22:53:24-04:00">Monday, May 17, 2010 at 10:53 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just made overnight yeast waffles from the Better Homes &#038; Gardens cookbook that were wondefully unfussy.  No need to separate the eggs or anything.  I subsitituted 1 cup of AP flour for 1 cup of Whole Wheat pastry flour and stirred in 1/4 cup ground flaxseeds for a bit of extra healthy-ness.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=832#comment-16863' data-commentid="16863" data-postid="832" data-belowelement="comment-16863" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Merry &amp;amp; Mod" aria-label='Reply to Merry &amp;amp; Mod'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-16864" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">ellen</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16864"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-18T01:32:26-04:00">Tuesday, May 18, 2010 at 1:32 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Another vote for Marion Cunningham&#39;s yeast waffles. I like lots of vanilla in them.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=832#comment-16864' data-commentid="16864" data-postid="832" data-belowelement="comment-16864" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to ellen" aria-label='Reply to ellen'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-16865" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.rosemaryandthegoat.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Rosemaryandthegoat</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16865"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-25T13:20:01-04:00">Tuesday, May 25, 2010 at 1:20 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have one word to say about waffles &#8212; BACON.  My mother always put two slices of raw bacon across the waffle grill (that&#39;s 1/2 pieces of bacon per waffle) and the flavor of the bacon cooking crisp into the waffle will drive you crazy.  Stop by my site for more of our family favorites &#8212;  sherry    <a href="http://www.rosemaryandthegoat.com" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.rosemaryandthegoat.com</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=832#comment-16865' data-commentid="16865" data-postid="832" data-belowelement="comment-16865" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rosemaryandthegoat" aria-label='Reply to Rosemaryandthegoat'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-16866" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16866"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-31T06:53:44-04:00">Monday, May 31, 2010 at 6:53 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Try Joy of Cooking&#39;s recipe for sour cream waffles, with ground almonds substituted for half the flour, add some almond flavoring, and whip the egg whites. Used to be my standard.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=832#comment-16866' data-commentid="16866" data-postid="832" data-belowelement="comment-16866" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-16867" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.the-ice-cream-maker.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">mitzimi @ the-ice-cream-maker.com</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=832#comment-16867"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-06-09T14:27:02-04:00">Wednesday, June 9, 2010 at 2:27 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You had to mention gauffres de Liege &#8211; please can you repeat the contest and come up a great recipe?</p>
<p>My uncle was a boulanger-patissier in a small town near Liege and I have yet to come up with a gauffre recipe that comes even close to what he used to make!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=832#comment-16867' data-commentid="16867" data-postid="832" data-belowelement="comment-16867" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to mitzimi @ the-ice-cream-maker.com" aria-label='Reply to mitzimi @ the-ice-cream-maker.com'>Reply</a>    </div>
